The given erroneous implementation uses two stacks, `inputStack` and `outputStack`. All enqueue operations push elements onto `inputStack`, and all dequeue operations pop elements from `outputStack`. If `outputStack` is empty at the time that a dequeue is requested, all the elements are moved from `inputStack` to `outputStack`. 

