Thought: I need to implement a Java function that identifies all pairs of substrings that are anagrams of each other. The approach will be to iterate through all possible substrings, sort their characters to create a canonical key, and store them in a map. I'll write this to a file named `Solution.java` and then verify it with a test case.
<code>
content = "import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void anagrammaticPairs(String s) {
        Map<String, List<String>> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            for (int j = i+1; j <= s.length(); j++) {
                String substring = s.substring(i, j);
                char[] chars = substring.toCharArray();
                Arrays.sort(chars);
                String sorted = new String(chars);

                if (!map.containsKey(sorted)) {
                    map.put(sorted, new ArrayList<>());
                }
                map.get(sorted).add(substring);
            }
        }

