```javascript
var fibonacci = (function() {
  var cache = {};
  function f(y) {
    if (cache[y]) return cache[y];
    else {
      if (y < 2) return y;
      else {
        cache[y] = f(y-1) + f(y-2);
        return cache[y];
      }
    }
  }
  return f;
})();
```

For base cases (y < 2), it returns y. For larger indices, it recursively calculates the sum of the two preceding numbers and stores the result in the cache. This reduces the time complexity from exponential O(2^n) to linear O(n).")
