var output = filterOddNumbers(arr);

console.log(output);
```

This function operates by checking each item in the array. If the item is a sub-array, it calls itself recursively to process the sub-array. If the item is an integer, it checks if the integer is odd by using the modulus operator. If the integer is odd (i.e., the remainder when divided by 2 is 1), it returns the integer; if the integer is even, it skips it by returning an empty array. The `flat()` function is used to flatten the result into a single array. The final output is an array of only the odd integers.")
